  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 604b577af8a43c942bd5251f25245dcd, type: 3}
  m_Name: VimanaShip_Lore
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::GV.UI.ShipLoreData
  shipName: Vimana Ship
  tagline: Two worlds fused into one hull. Neither side trusts it. Both sides need
    it.
  rarity: Rare
  shipClass: Hybrid Assault Carrier
  originLabel: Joint Program
  originName: Akasa Raajyas - Earth Countries
  factionLabel: Pilots
  factionName: Sarathi & Atom Riders
  powerSystem: Dual-Core Thara-Nuclear Reactor
  combatRole: Adaptive multi-theater strike platform
  specialAbility: "Resonance Shift - toggles between Thara Mode (divine-alloy shields,
    Astra weapon boost, self-repair) and Nuclear Mode (reactor overclock, rapid-fire
    hardpoints, targeting computer override). Switching takes three seconds and leaves
    the ship vulnerable during transition."
  backstory: "The Vimana Ship was never supposed to exist. After the Battle of Garuda
    Vana's Lower Peaks - the first engagement where Atom Rider Spaceships fought Sarathi
    Vimanas to a standstill - both sides realized something dangerous. Neither could
    destroy the other. The Kingdoms had divine armor and limitless Thara energy but
    their ancient weapons lacked the precision of modern targeting systems. The Countries
    had raw Nuclear-P firepower and modular hardpoints but their manufactured hulls
    cracked under sustained Astra bombardment. A rogue coalition formed in secret.
    Garudaja wind-readers who had grown tired of the Devas claiming ownership of every
    Vimana. QiNEXi engineers from Silkvale who wanted to push reactor technology beyond
    anything a pure Spaceship could handle. INTARi operatives who saw an opportunity
    to broker power between both worlds. They stole a dormant Vimana from Ratna Shila's
    sealed vaults and dragged it to an underground hangar in Elgorn Fall. For two years
    they cut into divine-alloy hull plating and welded Nuclear-P reactor housing alongside
    the ancient Thara Core. Half the engineering team died when the first dual-core
    ignition caused a resonance cascade that leveled the hangar. The second attempt
    worked. The Vimana Ship flies on two hearts - one ancient, one manufactured. It
    can switch between power sources mid-flight, adapting to any battlefield. The Kingdoms
    call it an abomination. The Countries call it a stolen weapon. The pilots who fly
    it call it the only ship that can survive what is coming."
  strengths: "Dual-core system allows switching between divine and nuclear power
    mid-combat\nDivine-alloy hull sections provide Vimana-class protection on critical
    components\nNuclear-P hardpoints deliver precision firepower that pure Vimanas
    lack\nAdaptive loadout - can be configured for either Thara-heavy or Nuclear-heavy
    operations depending on the mission"
  weaknesses: "Resonance Shift transition leaves the ship defenseless for three
    seconds\nDual-core synchronization is fragile - heavy damage can knock one core
    offline permanently\nNeither Sarathi nor Atom Rider maintenance crews fully
    understand the other half of the ship\nExtremely rare - each one is hand-built
    from a salvaged Vimana hull, and there are very few dormant Vimanas left"
  history: "Battle of Garuda Vana's Lower Peaks ends in stalemate between Spaceships
    and Vimanas\nRogue Garudaja and QiNEXi engineers form a secret coalition in Elgorn
    Fall\nINTARi operatives steal a dormant Vimana from Ratna Shila's sealed vaults\nFirst
    dual-core ignition fails catastrophically - resonance cascade destroys the underground
    hangar\nSecond prototype achieves stable Thara-Nuclear synchronization\nKingdoms
    of Nandana and Daitya Giri denounce the project as sacrilege against divine
    vessels\nEarth Countries demand the technology be surrendered to military command\nVimana
    Ship pilots refuse both sides and operate as an independent faction"
